    "synopsis": "Mozart’s most beloved comedy, The Marriage of Figaro is returning to our stage after a decade. This production leans into the lush, maximalist world of 18th-century “Marie Antoinette” style. While Figaro tries to outsmart the philandering Count Almaviva, it is ultimately the brilliant Susanna and the resilient Countess who pull the strings to save the wedding day. It’s a gorgeous, traditional romp through the complexities of human nature, filled with Mozart’s most sublime melodies and a heart that beats for justice and forgiveness.",
